commitResults.messageBody:
The adding and deleting of tasks and links is unintuitive as it
redirects user back to the home page.

Let's enforce a restriction on the adding and deleting of tasks and links
such that task and link commands are enabled only when the module can be seen from
the GUI interface (e.g at homepage or at module page etc)

FindModuleCommand and ListModuleCommand have been updated to only
work when user is in home page.

Currently, there are no details in the user guide that specifies how can users add and delete contacts.

Thus, this pull request aims to update user guide with details on addition and deletion of contacts.

In addition, this pull request fixes some formatting issues.

commitResults.messageBody:
Currently, there exists a way to add a contact into Plannit. The current implementation captures information like
address and associate tags to the contact.

This needs to change as,
* such information does not align with our goal for Plannit, which is to use it as an academic planner that stores
useful module related information.
* the current tag system allows for any string to be a tag, and we want to only allow module code to be a tag (in
future milestones).

Implement add contact command to align with Plannit's goal.
* Has name, email, phone field
* Does not have an address field
* Does not have tags field

Lines related to tags have been removed from the code base as the current milestone has no requirement for tags.
However if time permits in future milestones, we may re-implement tags assoicated to contacts, but with different
specifications.

Some related-tasks left to do:
* Clean up the EditCommand class (to ensure no more mentioning of address and tags)
* Delete the old AddCommand class and other classes that are assoicated to it (including in test)
* Clean up the code in the testing section (like PersonBuilder) to ensure there's no more mentioning of address and
tags
* Unit tests for the new AddContactCommand class
